## Phase 1: Object Detection

### 1.1 Object specification — 2026-05-04 — DONE

**Method:** user-provided physical inspection of the actual target
object (replaces assumption of a plain colored cube). Verified live
with the camera + dt_apriltags.

**Specification:**

| Property | Value |
|---|---|
| Shape | cuboid (NOT cube) |
| Dimensions | 30 × 30 × 60 mm |
| Color | red on 5 faces |
| Special face | one 30×30 mm face has an AprilTag |
| Tag family | tag36h11 |
| Tag ID | 3 |
| Tag black-square edge | ~19 mm (corner span 46.2 px @ z=200 mm, fx=479.47) |
| Lighting | indoor LED overhead, blinds drawn, minimal shadows |

**Implication for design:** the cuboid is a richer detection target
than a plain colored cube. We get **two complementary detection
paths** instead of one:
- **AprilTag track** (when tag face visible): full 6-DOF pose, ~5 mm /
  1° accuracy at the calibrated tag size.
- **HSV red track** (always-on fallback): 2D bbox + depth-lift centroid
  + yaw from `cv2.minAreaRect`. Medium accuracy (~20 mm / 10° in good
  light).

The cuboid's 1:2 aspect ratio (`asp = max(w,h)/min(w,h) ≈ 1.5–2.0` as
projected) is also useful for rejecting non-cube clutter (hands, mugs)
which typically have aspect ratios <1.4.

**Plan changes:** `initial_tasks` Phase 1 was rewritten on 2026-05-04
to reflect the dual-track architecture. Originally specced as
"BGR→HSV → contour → bbox" only; now specced as "AprilTag preferred,
HSV fallback, priority router".

